  <p><br><br>

  <b>WEB DEVELOPER:</b><br>
    This system was created and maintained by May Florence Javellana-Franco. She is currently connected with Iloilo Science and Technology University or ISAT U (formerly known as Western Visayas College of Science and Technology
    or WVCST).<br><br>

  <b>OBJECTIVES:</b><br>

  Generally, this system was developed as an Online Post Disaster Impact Assessment and Decision Support Response System for the Island of Guimaras.<br><br>

Specifically, this system was developed with the following features:<br>
1.  Expedite the response of responsible agencies after disaster strikes by <br>
a.  automatically assessing the impact of a disaster to provide fast analysis of needs of the affected populations <br>
b.  being able to send alert messages through SMS to responsible agencies for fast notification<br>
c.  being able to provide suggestions on the best possible route from the source area to the affected areas for fast delivery of needed services.<br><br>

2.  To be able to generate a list of the kinds and volume of relief aids needed per family affected for a fair, precise and timely allocation and distribution.<br><br>

3.  To be able to implement community-based ICT by remotely gathering from each barangay the validated data for pre-storing, the type of hazard or calamity that has hit, the list of affected populations, and road status. <br><br>

